* BMAP IDRP refinements (deferred #3): nested IDRP and the literal-list form.
*   PAIR: an outer "IDRP #1" containing an inner "IDRP #2" -- the body (OCT #1 /
*         OCT #2) is emitted for every (#1,#2) pair.  PAIR (1,2),(7,8) ->
*         1,7,1,8 (for #1=1) then 2,7,2,8 (for #1=2).
*   EMIT: a literal-list "IDRP (5,6,7)" -- the inline list is bound to the
*         block's dummy parameter #9.  -> OCT 5,6,7.
       OUNAME IDRP2
PAIR   MACRO
       IDRP   #1
       IDRP   #2
       OCT    #1
       OCT    #2
       IDRP
       IDRP
       ENDM
EMIT   MACRO
       IDRP   (5,6,7)
       OCT    #9
       IDRP
       ENDM
       PAIR   (1,2),(7,8)
       EMIT
       END
